span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Gill Sans MT&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\nArial;color:#475055\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Gill Sans MT&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\nArial;color:#475055\">A dispute resolution cum amnesty scheme called the Sabka\nVishwas Legacy Dispute Resolution Scheme is being introduced for resolution and\nsettlement of legacy cases of Central Excise and Service Tax.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; line-height: 150%; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Gill Sans MT&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\ncolor:#47525E\">This scheme has aimed to unlock over Rs 3.75 lakh crore involved\nin pending cases related to service tax and excise duty.The relief proposed\nunder the scheme varies from 40 per cent to 70 per cent of the tax dues for\ncases other than voluntary disclosure cases, depending on the amount of tax\ndues involved.</span><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Gill Sans MT&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\nmso-bidi-font-family:Arial;color:#475055\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; backgro