 line-height: 150%; font-family: &quot;Gill Sans MT&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">On August 20, 2019 vide Notification No. 36/2019-Central Tax,\nCBIC has extended the date from August 21, 2019 to November 21, 2019 from which\nno person (including a consignor, consignee, transporter, an e-commerce\noperator or a courier agency) shall be allowed to generate an e-way bill, if he\nhas not furnished the returns for two consecutive tax periods.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;line-height:150%;\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\nline-height:150%;font-family:&quot;Gill Sans MT&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:\n&quot;Gill Sans MT&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Gill Sans MT&quot;\">2.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:&quot;Gill Sans MT&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">The\nabove said Notification will prohibit a person to generate Part-A of Form GST\nEWB-01 who failed to submit returns for two consecutive period or months. To\nbetter understand the above notification which prohibits the person from\ngeneration of E-way Bill from 21 November 2019 we can take an example:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\nline-height:150%;font-family:&quot;Gill Sans MT&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"margin-left:1.0in;mso-add-space:auto;\ntext-indent:-31.5pt;line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:\n150%;font-family:&quot;Gill Sans MT&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">Ex 1:&nbsp; If any person not furnishes his monthly returns\nfor two consecutive tax periods like September and October 2019 till due date i.e.\n20 November 2019 for furnishing the same then that person will not be able to generate\nE-way bill from 21 November 2019 for transportation of goods.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-left:1.0in;mso-add-space:\nauto;text-indent:-31.5pt;line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\nline-height:150%;font-family:&quot;Gill Sans MT&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"margin-left:1.0in;mso-add-space:auto;\ntext-indent:-31.5pt;line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:\n150%;font-family:&quot;Gill Sans MT&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">Ex 2:&nbsp; Further, in case of any person required to\nfile quarterly return then he has to file his April to June 2019 and July to\nSeptember 2019 return upto 20<sup>th</sup> November 2019 if he failed to submit\nthe both return then he will not be able to generate E-way Bill from 21<sup>st</sup>\nNovember 2019 for transportation of goods.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\nline-height:150%;font-family:&quot;Gill Sans MT&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;line-height:150%;\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\nline-height:150%;font-family:&quot;Gill Sans MT&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:\n&quot;Gill Sans MT&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Gill Sans MT&quot;\">3.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:&quot;Gill Sans MT&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">Further,\nthe only remedy available to such person regarding the prohibition for\ngeneration of Part A of E-way bill, either he can file the GST return or file an\napplication before jurisdictional Commissioner requesting to allow him to\ngenerate E-way bill. After said application the Commissioner may allow the\nperson on sufficient cause being shown and for reasons to be recorded in\nwriting after giving the person a reasonable opportunity of being heard.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;font-family:&quot;Gill Sans MT&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Gill Sans MT&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(15, 15, 15); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Hope the above-mentioned details will help you.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: &quot;Gill Sans MT&quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(15, 15, 15); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial